1
00:00:00,140 --> 00:00:05,210
In this video, we are going to learn when not to use microservices.

2
00:00:05,210 --> 00:00:09,590
That means anti-patterns of usage microservices.

3
00:00:09,890 --> 00:00:14,180
The first anti-pattern is don't do distributed monolithic.

4
00:00:14,750 --> 00:00:22,250
Make sure that you decompose your services properly and respecting the decoupling rule like applying

5
00:00:22,250 --> 00:00:24,650
bounded context and business capabilities.

6
00:00:24,650 --> 00:00:25,490
Principles.

7
00:00:26,950 --> 00:00:30,730
Otherwise you are losing the benefits of microservices.

8
00:00:30,760 --> 00:00:35,020
Also, make sure that services should be loosely coupling.

9
00:00:35,620 --> 00:00:42,730
If your services has chatty communication with strong coupling, you will end up with highly coupled

10
00:00:42,730 --> 00:00:43,960
service architecture.

11
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:50,530
That means you have developed a distributed monolithic architecture which comes with none of the benefits

12
00:00:50,530 --> 00:00:52,390
of microservices should be doing.

13
00:00:53,770 --> 00:01:01,000
Distributed monolithic architecture is the worst case because you increase the complexity of your architecture

14
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:04,330
without getting any benefit of microservices.

15
00:01:04,950 --> 00:01:07,830
Microservices are all about autonomy.

16
00:01:07,860 --> 00:01:10,650
When you lose or lose the autonomy.

17
00:01:10,680 --> 00:01:17,340
Teams must coordinate during the development and deployment, and teams will highly dependent on each

18
00:01:17,340 --> 00:01:17,970
other.

19
00:01:18,150 --> 00:01:22,560
By the time you will lose your agility of new feature deployments.

20
00:01:23,640 --> 00:01:30,450
So if you end up with distributed monolithic application, has a higher latency and application can

21
00:01:30,450 --> 00:01:38,130
have synchronization issues and application is a lot harder to manage and debug when something breaks.

22
00:01:38,160 --> 00:01:40,650
Coupled services are hard to debug.

23
00:01:41,600 --> 00:01:47,840
The second antipattern is don't do microservices without DevOps or cloud services.

24
00:01:48,140 --> 00:01:54,830
Microservices are embraced the distributed cloud native approaches, and you can only maximize benefits

25
00:01:54,830 --> 00:01:58,940
of microservices with following these cloud native principles.

26
00:02:00,080 --> 00:02:07,250
Some of these principles are CI CD pipeline with DevOps automations, proper deployment and monitoring

27
00:02:07,280 --> 00:02:07,880
tools.

28
00:02:07,880 --> 00:02:11,630
Managed cloud services to support your infrastructure.

29
00:02:11,630 --> 00:02:15,950
Follow key enabling technologies and tools like containers.

30
00:02:15,950 --> 00:02:22,580
Orchestrator, Docker and Kubernetes broke the dependencies with following asynchronous communications

31
00:02:22,580 --> 00:02:26,120
using messaging and even event streaming services.

32
00:02:27,470 --> 00:02:33,740
If you don't follow these principles in microservice architecture, you will again end up with distributed

33
00:02:33,740 --> 00:02:40,100
monolithic, which is the worst case because you increase complexity of your architecture without getting

34
00:02:40,100 --> 00:02:41,960
any benefit of microservices.

